rs experience in mapping new words and structures onto real-world referents? The contributors to this volume put forth a novel approach to second language learning, presenting it as a process that involves conceptual development and restructuring, and not simply the mapping of new forms onto pre-existing meanings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aBilingualism. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching. 0aSecond language acquisition. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aAmeel, Eef, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAthanasopoulos, Panos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBylund, Emanuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarroll, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGullberg, Marianne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalt, Barbara C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPavlenko, Aneta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPavlenko, Aneta, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchmiedtová, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStutterheim, Christiane von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184769338940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847693389423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847693389/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 200